  "text": "• Our bounds for BFS and DFS in the rotate and implicit models immediately imply (with some care) similar bounds, that are improvement over the best space bounds known so far in ROM, for many applications of DFS/BFS. Moreover, as described before, any algorithm in the rotate model can be implemented in ROM using extra O(n lg(m/n)) bits. Thus, our linear time DFS algorithm in the rotate model can be implemented in ROM using O(n lg(m/n)) bits, matching the bound of [CITATION_1] for DFS. Using this DFS implementation, we can obtain improved space efficient algorithms for various applications of DFS in ROM. This is discussed in Section 8.1.",
